{
  "texts": [
    "In 5 cases publishers either corrected articles with failed fact checks or shifted their editorial policies, resulting in a label shift from unreliable -to reliable +.",
    "Beyond errors in the article-publisher and publisher-label mappings, the texts themselves frequently contain duplicates or scraping errors.",
    "Of the 6.7M re-labelled articles, roughly ≈ 22% or 1.5M articles were duplicates.",
    "Many of the remaining unique articles were deemed malformed or semantically void.",
    "These contain either very little text, substantial amounts of markup or include too many special tokens to be human-readable."
  ]
}